{
  "text": "We find a strong decrease in FR (Fig. 2) and \"allocation to above-ground structure\" (Table 2) for Southeast China, where rainfall is predicted to increase rather than decrease (IPCC, 2007) . This result is antipodal to the findings of [CITATION_1] , who predicted an increase in species richness for that region. This somewhat counterintuitive result is associated with a trend to increasing values in the functional trait \"seed size\" (t11, Table 1), i.e. towards bigger seeds, under future climates (Fig. 4) .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "215537431"
